Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in mathematics would. What is the name of CC1CCCCC(C1)I
Answer:
gpt_response: The compound CC1CCCCC(C1)I is known as 1-iodoadamantane. The structure consists of a cyclohexyl ring with a cyclopentane ring attached to one of its carbons, which is in turn bonded to an iodine atom. The compound belongs to the class of adamantanes, which are polycyclic hydrocarbons known for their unique structure and chemical properties.
